# üìã Clip Vault Ultimate (v0.2.1)

**Clip Vault** is a professional, lightweight, and cross-platform (optimized for Linux) clipboard manager. It is designed for power users who need a secure way to store their clipboard history with full support for **Persian (Farsi/Arabic)** and **English** languages.



---

## ‚ú® Features

* **Dual-Language Search:** Seamlessly search through your history in both English and Farsi.
* **Farsi Smart-Input:** Innovative "Invisible Overlay" technology to fix the common Farsi character disconnection bug in Linux GUI environments.
* **Global Hotkey:** Toggle the app window instantly from anywhere in your system using `Ctrl + Space`.
* **System Tray Integration:** Runs quietly in the background; access it via the system tray icon.
* **Persistent Database:** Powered by SQLite with a versioning system for safe future updates.
* **Lightweight & Fast:** Minimal resource usage, built with CustomTkinter.
* **Automatic Startup:** Includes a script to easily add the app to your Linux Autostart.

---

## üöÄ Installation (Linux)

### 1. Prerequisites
Ensure you have Python 3.10+ and the following system libraries:
```bash
sudo pacman -S fuse2 noto-fonts  # For Arch Linux
# OR
sudo apt install libfuse2 fonts-noto-core  # For Ubuntu/Debian

```

### 2. Setup Environment

```bash
git clone [https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/ClipVault.git](https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/ClipVault.git)
cd ClipVault
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt

```

### 3. Binary Build & Install

To install the app as a native binary in your system menu:

```bash
# Build the binary
pyinstaller --noconfirm --onefile --windowed --name ClipVault --hidden-import pystray --hidden-import PIL --hidden-import bidi --hidden-import arabic_reshaper --collect-all customtkinter main.py

# Run the installer
python install_binary.py

```

---

## ‚å®Ô∏è Usage

* **Show/Hide Window:** Press `Ctrl + Space`.
* **Search:** Type in the search bar. Use the **EN/FA** toggle button for RTL/LTR search optimization.
* **Copy:** Click on any clip to copy it back to your clipboard.
* **Delete:** Right-click on any clip to remove it from history.
* **Exit:** Right-click the tray icon and select **Quit**.

---

## üõ† Tech Stack

* **GUI:** [CustomTkinter](https://github.com/TomSchimansky/CustomTkinter)
* **Database:** SQLite3
* **Text Processing:** `arabic-reshaper`, `python-bidi`
* **Hotkey Management:** `pynput`
* **Tray Icon:** `pystray`

